Date:  0/0/1966
Source:  English Language in Aust. & NZ, The
Author:  TURNER
Vol / Page:  115
Edition:
Quote:  There is simile: `as mad as a snake', `as bald as a bandicoot' (an embroidery on the English `bald as a coot'), `as happy as larry', `rough as bags' (which I know better in the variant `rough as sacks'), `as wet as a shag'.
